subSubSection.paragraph:
Clypeus almost flat, with a weak transverse ridge near apex; malar space 0.6–0.8× as long as basal mandibular width (
Fig. 24
); lower face at narrowest point 0.9× as wide as height from clypeofacial suture to insertion of antenna; hypostomal carina joined to occipital carina far from base of mandible; posterior ocellus separated the eye by 1.3–1.5× its own maximum diameter (
Fig. 27
); antenna with first flagellomere about 0.9–1.0× as long as the second; subapical flagellomeres slightly elongated.

Tergite I slender, 3.0–4.0× as long as posteriorly broad; sternite I short, reaching about 0.3–0.4 of length of tergite, with a median swelling centrally; tergite II 1.4–2.3× as long as broad, with isolated pubescence; tergite VII mediodorsally without an indentation posteriorly; tergite VIII, in lateral view, tapered to a bluntly rounded apex, without a cornus, and with uniformly scattered pubescence (
Fig. 23
); tergite IX bearing long pubescence; ovipositor at rest extending beyond apex of metasoma by 3.5–4.5× the length of the hind tibia.

paragraph.materialsCitation:
Lectotype ♀ , (
Apechoneura nigriventris Mocsáry
